---
import Section from '../ui/Section.astro';
import TextReveal from '../interactive/TextReveal.jsx';
import FadeIn from '../interactive/FadeIn.jsx';
---

<Section id="synopsis" padding="xl">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <FadeIn client:visible>
      <p class="text-gold font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-sm mb-4 text-center">
        The Story
      </p>
    </FadeIn>

    <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-medium text-center mb-12 leading-tight">
      <TextReveal client:visible>
        Two timelines. Two loves. One ancient truth.
      </TextReveal>
    </h2>

    <div class="prose prose-lg md:prose-xl mx-auto text-ink/80 leading-relaxed">
      <FadeIn client:visible delay={0.2}>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl leading-relaxed mb-8">
          The novella moves between two worlds: a fictional contemporary False Bay, and the ancient city of Ugarit on the Levantine coast, some six thousand years ago.
        </p>
      </FadeIn>

      <FadeIn client:visible delay={0.3}>
        <p class="mb-6">
          In the present, Eliot—an old man recovering from a stroke—believes himself to be God. He sees everything: past, present, future, every thought of every living thing. Until he meets a woman called D, a blind spot in his omniscience. Through caring for her, he learns how love lies in care.
        </p>
      </FadeIn>

      <FadeIn client:visible delay={0.4}>
        <p class="mb-6">
          In the past, two people who believe they are El and Asherah—the great Levantine deities—act out their mythic relationship. When their love falls apart, so does the ancient city they inhabit.
        </p>
      </FadeIn>

      <FadeIn client:visible delay={0.5}>
        <p class="text-lg italic text-ink/60 border-l-2 border-gold/40 pl-6 my-10">
          "A meditation on what it means to truly know another person—and whether anyone, even a god, can claim such knowledge."
        </p>
      </FadeIn>
    </div>
  </div>
</Section>
